Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with Dynamic Frame Aloha (DFA) in Radio Frequency Identification (RFID) environment, which is a networking and communication technology. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the efficiency of backlog estimation procedures, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an improvement to an existing backlog estimation procedure, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the efficiency of different backlog estimation procedures, which is related to performance analysis. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with a system of tags in a RFID environment, which can be seen as a multiagent system.
